                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320517-238-victim1780 t18320517-238-viclabel1376"></join> in a merchant's office. I was in <placeName id="t18320517-238-crimeloc1377">Old-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320517-238-crimeloc1377" type="placeName" value="Old-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320517-238-crimeloc1377" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320517-238-off1374 t18320517-238-crimeloc1377"></join> between seven and eight o'clock on the 10th of May - I was told I had lost my handkerchief, and missed it; I did not see the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320517-238-person1782">
                  WILLIAM 
                  COLTON
               <interp inst="t18320517-238-person1782" type="surname" value="COLTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320517-238-person1782" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320517-238-person1782" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I saw the two prisoners follow this gentleman and another down Old-street: and before they got to Golden-lane, I saw Diacre take this handkerchief and give it to Markes - I sent Cadby, who was with me, to tell the gentleman; and in going along Goswell-street we took the prisoners in company again - we put them into a shop, and this handkerchief was picked up there.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320517-238-person1783">
                  JOSEPH 
                  CADBY
               <interp inst="t18320517-238-person1783" type="surname" value="CADBY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320517-238-person1783" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320517-238-person1783" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoners take the handkerchief, and I have had it ever since.</p>
               <p>The prisoners put in a written Defence, stating that they had found the handkerchief on the pavement.</p>
